# TeleHealthy Media Capture

## Captured assets

### Screenshots (7 total, 602 KB)
1. **01-hero-landing.png** (74 KB)
   - Initial app load: "Inbound Voice Ops Console" hero heading, "Simulate Inbound Call" CTA button visible, clean layout with tabbed interface (Inbound / Outbound / CRM / Analytics), sidebar showing SMS LOG section.

2. **02-intent-options.png** (53 KB)
   - After "Simulate Inbound Call" clicked: Six intent buttons displayed (Book / Hours / Insurance / Telehealth / This is urgent / End Call), demonstrating the natural conversation flow for incoming call routing.

3. **03-booking-intent.png** (93 KB)
   - "Book an appointment" selected: AI confidence badge shows 88%, transcript area shows AI greeting ("Thank you for calling..."), New Patient chip prompt visible for user to select, illustrating multi-turn booking conversation.

4. **04-new-patient-response.png** (101 KB)
   - "New Patient" selected: AI responds with follow-up prompt, SMS LOG shows confirmation message (SMS sent), transcript continues naturally, full booking context captured (patient type → next phase).

5. **05-warm-transfer-escalation.png** (94 KB)
   - "This is urgent" path: Call status changes to **TRANSFERRING**, AI confidence drops to 34% (🚨 ESCALATE badge), AI message: "Let me connect you with one of our care coordinators right away. Please hold.", demonstrates escalation logic and warm-transfer trigger.

6. **06-analytics-dashboard.png** (108 KB)
   - Analytics tab: Shows call metrics (155 total calls, 67% booking rate, 8% escalation rate, 0.79 avg AI confidence, 2m14s avg handle time), bar charts and KPI cards visible, demonstrates production-grade call center analytics.

7. **07-outbound-crm-contacts.png** (79 KB)
   - Outbound tab: CRM CONTACTS list showing 8 patients (Maria Santos, James Whitfield, Sofia Reyes, David Kim + 4 more), columns visible: patient name, provider, visit history, appointment status, ready for outbound dialer demonstration.

### Video (714 KB)
**hero-flow-demo.webm** (1400×900, ~12s)
- Deterministic playback of hero inbound booking flow: page load → Simulate Inbound Call → Book intent → New Patient response → SMS confirmation in sidebar → End Call. Captures natural UI state transitions and real-time transcript growth. Suitable for deck slide show or live demo reference.

